content.text:
Let me analyze the target structure and provide a detailed solution.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
The structure consists of two distinct parts:
1. A "house-like" structure on the left made of:
   - Red arch base
   - Green rectangular block on top
   - Blue cube with orange triangular roof
   - Orange cylindrical tower with triangular roof

2. A "vehicle-like" structure on the right made of:
   - Two orange horizontal cylinders as wheels
   - Yellow rectangular platform
   - Blue cube on top

Total blocks used: 9 blocks
Layers: Maximum 3 layers in the house structure

Block Selection and Assembly Order:
For the house structure (left to right):
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1 (red arch)
    Step2: Move block with index 6 (green rectangle)
    Step3: Move block with index 3 (blue cube)
    Step4: Move block with index 9 (orange cylinder)
    Step5: Move block with index 13 (orange triangle roof)
    Step6: Move block with index 14 (orange triangle roof)
}

For the vehicle structure (left to right):
{
    Step7: Move block with index 10 (orange cylinder)
    Step8: Move block with index 10 (orange cylinder again)
    Step9: Move block with index 7 (yellow rectangle)
    Step10: Move block with index 3 (blue cube)
}

The blocks are selected to match exactly as they appear in both orientation and color from the dictionary image, with no rotations needed.
